1
00:00:02,030 --> 00:01:33,290
♪

2
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:49,220
♪

3
00:01:49,220 --> 00:01:51,886
What the--?

4
00:01:51,886 --> 00:01:53,008
We did it!

5
00:01:53,008 --> 00:01:54,140
It was us!

6
00:01:54,140 --> 00:01:56,030
(laughter)

7
00:01:56,030 --> 00:02:00,020
You two really had me going.

8
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:01,270
He's so gentle and kind...

9
00:02:01,270 --> 00:02:03,270
he can't be a killer.

10
00:02:03,270 --> 00:02:07,130
Ah, now that's clean!

11
00:02:07,130 --> 00:02:09,180
Oh, now that's really clean!

12
00:02:09,180 --> 00:02:11,200
(laughs)

13
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:14,010
Ah, it's a beautiful day!

14
00:02:14,010 --> 00:02:20,190
♪

15
00:02:20,190 --> 00:02:23,070
Mmm, it's peaceful.

16
00:02:23,070 --> 00:02:28,100
♪

17
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:30,060
This feels good.

18
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:31,210
You need a bath, Kenshin!

19
00:02:31,210 --> 00:02:32,220
Don't get me wet!

20
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:33,280
Too peaceful.

21
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,090
Come on, let's get charged!

22
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:37,250
(grunting)

23
00:02:37,250 --> 00:02:39,030
What's that?

24
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,140
How come

25
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:42,080
there are

26
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:45,150
no students coming in here?

27
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:47,280
The Battousai
impersonator incident is over,

28
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:50,240
so how come martial arts
students aren't joining up?

29
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:52,060
I know!

30
00:02:52,060 --> 00:02:54,160
After all, I am a cute teacher.

31
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:56,140
Maybe I'm so beautiful
that students are just

32
00:02:56,140 --> 00:02:58,030
plain scared away?

33
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:01,100
Maybe it's just
a matter of me being born

34
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,280
under a really unlucky star?

35
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:04,250
It just doesn't seem fair!

36
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:06,180
(crying)

37
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:07,714
How long have you been there?

38
00:03:07,714 --> 00:03:08,230
Sorry.

39
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:09,220
It's all right.

40
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:11,130
I know that students
will come back to study

41
00:03:11,130 --> 00:03:13,140
here at Kamiya Dojo, but when?

42
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:15,130
Miss Kori,
don't get so anxious.

43
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:16,030
Why not?

44
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,010
You can be a student.

45
00:03:17,010 --> 00:03:18,170
How am I supposed
to keep my skills sharp

46
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:20,120
if you won't even
fence with me?

47
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,020
No, wooden swords
is not something

48
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:23,150
that I'm very good at.

49
00:03:23,150 --> 00:03:25,180
Hey, Kori, I'm getting hungry.

50
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:26,200
I'm starving!

51
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:28,160
Me, too, so?

52
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:30,210
Dr. Gensai,
it's good to see you.

53
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,280
Hello, all.

54
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:33,110
So, what you got for lunch?

55
00:03:33,110 --> 00:03:35,130
Hmm, I've got it!

56
00:03:35,130 --> 00:03:37,230
On a day like this,
we should all be cheerful.

57
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:39,180
Why's that?

58
00:03:39,180 --> 00:03:41,060
'Cause you're paying

59
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,060
for all of us.

60
00:03:42,060 --> 00:03:56,260
♪

61
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:58,160
Boy, do I feel lucky!

62
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:01,210
I just came by to say
hi to my granddaughters.

63
00:04:01,210 --> 00:04:03,250
Kenshin likes
to treat us to lunch.

64
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:05,250
I'll split some
chow mein with these two.

65
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,230
Chow mein!

66
00:04:07,230 --> 00:04:10,120
Ugh, I think chow mein stinks!

67
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,210
Huh?

68
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:13,200
Hmm.

69
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:15,190
Yeah, that's it!

70
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:24,270
Wait a second!

71
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:27,040
I haven't moved,
you want that?

72
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,290
Wow, you'll buy that for me?

73
00:04:28,290 --> 00:04:30,140
Sure.

74
00:04:30,140 --> 00:04:31,150
Yay!

75
00:04:31,150 --> 00:04:33,000
I'm glad you're happy.

76
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:33,838
Huh, what?

77
00:04:33,838 --> 00:04:35,180
Huh?

78
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:37,250
I hadn't even noticed
that I dropped that.

79
00:04:39,348 --> 00:04:40,260
Huh?

80
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:43,080
Hey, get your hands off me!

81
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:47,180
Say, it's nice you gave
him his wallet back.

82
00:04:47,180 --> 00:04:50,040
Kenshin, I knew you'd run off
when it's time to treat us,

83
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,080
now come on!

84
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:54,270
He could have turned me in.

85
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:57,030
Look at that man,
he's got a sword!

86
00:04:57,030 --> 00:04:58,230
It's been two years
since wearing one's

87
00:04:58,230 --> 00:05:00,030
been outlawed.

88
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:02,020
I guess some samurais
just can't let go

89
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:04,150
of the old ways,
no matter what.

90
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:17,260
♪

91
00:05:17,260 --> 00:05:19,130
-Huh?
-Huh?

92
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:21,240
♪

93
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,250
Hey, this kid is a pickpocket.

94
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:25,220
He stole your wallet.

95
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:28,200
Hey, ugly, what else can you do?

96
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,140
Yeah?

97
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:30,220
Well, for starters,
I can tell you

98
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:32,080
that's no way to talk to a lady,

99
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,180
you purse-stealing punk!

100
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:34,250
Stop screaming!

101
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:37,110
Stop, that's enough.

102
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:40,040
Thanks for catching this guy
and saving my wallet, Kori.

103
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,090
Don't try it again.

104
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:47,200
♪

105
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,010
Huh?

106
00:05:49,010 --> 00:05:50,120
Let's go.

107
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,130
Kenshin!

108
00:05:51,130 --> 00:05:56,150
♪

109
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:57,170
Ow!

110
00:05:57,170 --> 00:05:59,160
♪

111
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:02,090
I'm not just a street kid,
my father was a samurai.

112
00:06:02,090 --> 00:06:03,230
I'm Yoshi Myojin!

113
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:06,230
I'm a Tokyo fujisoku
and I've never accepted charity

114
00:06:06,230 --> 00:06:09,020
from anybody and
I'm not starting now!

115
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:10,210
If you think you
and your ugly friend

116
00:06:10,210 --> 00:06:12,190
are helping me
by giving me a break,

117
00:06:12,190 --> 00:06:13,240
guess again!

118
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:15,150
You two trolls
wouldn't stand a chance

119
00:06:15,150 --> 00:06:16,290
against me if I
decided to fight,

120
00:06:16,290 --> 00:06:18,220
so bug off before you get hurt!

121
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:21,210
Listen up, kid--

122
00:06:21,210 --> 00:06:23,270
Get it straight,
I'm not a kid!

123
00:06:23,270 --> 00:06:26,090
Please listen, I know
you've grown up fast

124
00:06:26,090 --> 00:06:27,260
living on the streets
by yourself, but you're

125
00:06:27,260 --> 00:06:29,100
still a kid at heart.

126
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:32,080
I apologize
if I offended you, Yoshi.

127
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,060
One more thing,
no one can ever

128
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,090
take your pride away.

129
00:06:35,090 --> 00:06:36,210
Oh?

130
00:06:36,210 --> 00:06:38,190
Hmph.

131
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:40,220
That's it, walk away.

132
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:41,270
Well, one thing's for sure,

133
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:44,070
he's a big-headed,
ill-tempered young man.

134
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:47,030
You can tell he's from
a samurai background.

135
00:06:47,030 --> 00:06:49,130
Twenty years ago, he might
have been a great samurai,

136
00:06:49,130 --> 00:06:51,090
but now's the wrong time.

137
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:03,180
"No one can ever
take your pride away."

138
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:06,060
I know, but how am I
gonna get out of this?

139
00:07:09,110 --> 00:07:11,000
Hello, Yoshi.

140
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:15,280
We've been looking
all over for you, Yoshi.

141
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:19,290
So, come on, give us
the money you made today.

142
00:07:19,290 --> 00:07:20,270
I don't have any!

143
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:22,090
What?

144
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:23,260
(grunts)

145
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:28,290
♪

146
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:33,070
Haven't I paid you back enough?

147
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:35,250
Well, I'd have to say no.

148
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:39,110
In 10 years, maybe 12 years,
or maybe you'd rather have us

149
00:07:39,110 --> 00:07:41,130
cut off your thumb instead?

150
00:07:49,170 --> 00:07:50,240
Waitress!

151
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,260
Yeah, over here please!

152
00:07:55,170 --> 00:07:57,100
So, what do you know
about this pickpocket?

153
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,150
Well, you see, he's an orphan.

154
00:07:59,150 --> 00:08:02,060
Both his parents passed
away when Yoshi was young.

155
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:03,260
Since then, the head
of the Shigumi has been

156
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:04,280
taking care of him.

157
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:06,030
Why the Shigumi?

158
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:08,270
You see, before she died,
Yoshi's mother was very ill

159
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:10,200
for a long time
and the Shigumi

160
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,180
covered all
her medical expenses.

161
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:14,250
So, as a result,
Yoshi owes the Shigumi

162
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:16,210
an incredible amount of money.

163
00:08:16,210 --> 00:08:18,090
Well, that explains a lot.

164
00:08:18,090 --> 00:08:20,160
So he's forced by those thugs
to work on the street to try

165
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,170
to pay off a huge debt.

166
00:08:22,170 --> 00:08:24,070
Yeah, poor kid.

167
00:08:24,070 --> 00:08:25,110
More hot pot, please!

168
00:08:25,110 --> 00:08:26,180
Yeah, more beef hot pot!

169
00:08:26,180 --> 00:08:28,160
All right, all right.

170
00:08:32,230 --> 00:08:36,120
That's not right,
I can't allow that to happen.

171
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:39,080
Hold it, where are you going?

172
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:41,210
To go find that kid,
I can't ignore this!

173
00:08:41,210 --> 00:08:43,060
Wait a minute.

174
00:08:43,060 --> 00:08:44,180
Are you trying to stop me?

175
00:08:44,180 --> 00:08:46,040
I've got to go help him!

176
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,080
Please, Kori.

177
00:08:52,210 --> 00:08:53,250
Kenshin, I can't believe

178
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:55,260
you're such
a cold-hearted person.

179
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:57,030
Kenshin!

180
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:59,060
Go boom-boom.

181
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:06,150
♪

182
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:09,120
Now, watch this.

183
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:12,050
Snake eyes, ha-ha!

184
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:14,090
They always come up snake eyes?

185
00:09:14,090 --> 00:09:15,190
They're loaded dice,
of course they'll

186
00:09:15,190 --> 00:09:17,110
always come up two.

187
00:09:17,110 --> 00:09:20,040
Yeah, these dice are
gonna make us lots of money.

188
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:22,010
(laughter)

189
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:29,070
I said I'm here to see Yoshi!

190
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,140
Who are you?

191
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:35,270
Did you come here
to try your luck

192
00:09:35,270 --> 00:09:37,060
and gamble with us?

193
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:39,070
I don't have
anything to say to you.

194
00:09:39,070 --> 00:09:41,220
I came here to talk to Yoshi.

195
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:44,130
You've got to quit this way
of life before it eats you up.

196
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:45,210
No matter what the reason,

197
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:47,170
a pickpocket is
just a pickpocket.

198
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:49,090
Now, come with me.

199
00:09:49,090 --> 00:09:51,050
But, you see, I can't.

200
00:09:51,050 --> 00:09:55,180
Young lady, so are you
a friend of Yoshi's?

201
00:09:55,180 --> 00:09:57,240
Hmm?

202
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,290
Hey, listen to me!

203
00:09:58,290 --> 00:10:00,180
She doesn't really know me!

204
00:10:01,599 --> 00:10:02,458
Take it easy!

205
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:04,210
Here is the situation
that Yoshi is in:

206
00:10:04,210 --> 00:10:07,030
He owes us a lot of money
and Yoshi must keep working

207
00:10:07,030 --> 00:10:08,220
for us in order to pay it back.

208
00:10:08,220 --> 00:10:10,250
That is, of course,
unless you are willing

209
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:13,260
to give us the money
to pay off his debt?

210
00:10:13,260 --> 00:10:16,020
So, how much money
are we talking about?

211
00:10:16,020 --> 00:10:18,050
Okay.

212
00:10:18,050 --> 00:10:19,130
Have a seat.

213
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:22,190
Huh?

214
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:26,210
♪

215
00:10:26,210 --> 00:10:29,270
The way we settle debts
around here is to play dice.

216
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:31,000
Oh.

217
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,040
Don't do it.

218
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:36,030
Play.

219
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:37,000
Okay, I'll do it.

220
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,220
But I have two
conditions to play.

221
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:41,090
Number one,
we only play one roll.

222
00:10:41,090 --> 00:10:43,170
The second condition,
if I win, all of you

223
00:10:43,170 --> 00:10:47,080
will leave Yoshi alone forever.

224
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:49,230
Agreed, and if you lose at dice,

225
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:51,040
then your payment
will be to work

226
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:54,070
as the maid here at
the Shigumi house for 20 years.

227
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:55,130
Agreed.

228
00:10:55,130 --> 00:10:56,280
Don't do it!

229
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,290
♪

230
00:10:58,290 --> 00:11:00,230
So, let's do it!

231
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:05,140
♪

232
00:11:07,090 --> 00:11:11,000
♪

233
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,160
So, let's do it!

234
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:19,270
Wait, I never asked
you for anything!

235
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:21,040
Why are you doing this?

236
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:23,000
It's stupid
to risk your freedom!

237
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,160
Yoshi, just shut your trap.

238
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:26,030
I'm here to give you some help.

239
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:27,150
I'm the one that's got
to save you from this

240
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:28,240
bunch of slime.

241
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:30,180
Huh?

242
00:11:30,180 --> 00:11:33,150
Hey, you got a lot
of guts for a woman.

243
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,270
But if you lose,
then you're really

244
00:11:34,270 --> 00:11:35,200
gonna have to--

245
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,080
I'm not going to lose, Yoshi.

246
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:39,100
I've always had
really good luck.

247
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:40,280
Yeah, I'll win!

248
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:42,010
I've got such a lucky streak

249
00:11:42,010 --> 00:11:43,250
that I can win
at almost any game.

250
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:45,160
Quiet down, let's roll!

251
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:47,090
Yeah, now stand aside!

252
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:53,030
Even number is "cho,"

253
00:11:53,030 --> 00:11:54,190
odd number is "han."

254
00:11:54,190 --> 00:11:55,130
You got it?

255
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:56,280
Yeah, I got it.

256
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:58,060
You call it, okay?

257
00:12:09,060 --> 00:12:10,070
I choose--

258
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:13,020
Cho.

259
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:14,080
Han.

260
00:12:17,250 --> 00:12:19,290
♪

261
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:22,000
It...it can't be!

262
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,050
Han!

263
00:12:23,050 --> 00:12:25,000
I knew it, I won!

264
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,270
How?

265
00:12:27,270 --> 00:12:30,140
I don't understand.

266
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:32,120
I won, come on,
let's go, Yoshi.

267
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:35,210
All right, she won,
so I want you to let her go!

268
00:12:35,210 --> 00:12:37,030
You can keep me!

269
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:39,170
Hey, just what are
you talking about?

270
00:12:39,170 --> 00:12:42,210
You don't understand,
these guys play for keeps.

271
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:46,150
You'll be lucky to get
out of here alive!

272
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:48,270
I knew it,
she replaced our dice!

273
00:12:56,140 --> 00:12:57,150
Huh?

274
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:59,010
So, you're the one?

275
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:04,010
Hmm.

276
00:13:08,010 --> 00:13:09,040
Hey, now.

277
00:13:10,190 --> 00:13:13,280
Nice try, Yoshi.

278
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,260
Too bad it failed.

279
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:20,130
Now what, buddy,
you wanna punch me back?

280
00:13:20,130 --> 00:13:23,130
Ooh!

281
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:26,110
Remember, no one
can take your pride away.

282
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:30,200
Hit me, hit me all you want.

283
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:32,060
But from now on,
I don't want anything

284
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:34,190
to do with you yakuzas.

285
00:13:34,190 --> 00:13:36,100
I'm done working
as a pickpocket

286
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:38,060
for you lowlifes
and I'm gonna find

287
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:40,200
myself an honest job
and I'll pay you all

288
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,240
that I owe.

289
00:13:47,090 --> 00:13:48,050
Huh?

290
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:53,280
Yoshi, that debt you owe us
for your mother's medical care

291
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:56,020
before she died, it was a lie!

292
00:13:56,020 --> 00:13:57,210
What?

293
00:13:57,210 --> 00:14:00,180
It was a lie we created
so we could own you forever.

294
00:14:00,180 --> 00:14:03,000
There was no debt,
it was just a clever excuse

295
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,020
so you would stay here
and serve us as a dog

296
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:06,120
the rest of your days!

297
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,290
Damn you!

298
00:14:14,110 --> 00:14:15,260
There you go, dog.

299
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:17,250
That's too much.

300
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:24,220
♪

301
00:14:24,220 --> 00:14:27,180
Don't worry, Yoshi,
I can handle 'em.

302
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:29,130
Now, it's your turn!

303
00:14:29,130 --> 00:14:46,260
♪

304
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:50,060
Well, your kendo skills
are very impressive for a woman,

305
00:14:50,060 --> 00:14:52,050
but wait, are you ready
to match skills with

306
00:14:52,050 --> 00:14:54,020
Gasuke the Killer?

307
00:14:54,020 --> 00:14:55,210
You men are all alike.

308
00:14:55,210 --> 00:15:09,100
♪

309
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,080
Gotcha!

310
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:16,150
♪

311
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:17,220
A dagger stick!

312
00:15:17,220 --> 00:15:20,040
It's time to get serious.

313
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:21,000
Stop it!

314
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,150
This is my trouble, not hers.

315
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:23,260
I'll save you!

316
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:30,150
Wait a moment, Gasuke.

317
00:15:30,150 --> 00:15:33,160
♪

318
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:35,020
I don't want to see
a woman's blood

319
00:15:35,020 --> 00:15:36,120
spilled during my lunch.

320
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:39,050
Kumicho?

321
00:15:39,050 --> 00:15:41,000
I want Yoshi right
in front of me now.

322
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:44,240
♪

323
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:47,140
Hey, show some respect.

324
00:15:47,140 --> 00:15:49,090
Come on!

325
00:15:49,090 --> 00:15:52,140
Yoshi, how were you planning
to earn a living if you stop

326
00:15:52,140 --> 00:15:54,290
pick-pocketing
and living the street life?

327
00:15:54,290 --> 00:15:56,250
Even if you are samurai-born,

328
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:58,010
these days that doesn't mean

329
00:15:58,010 --> 00:16:00,150
a hill of beans
in our Meiji era.

330
00:16:00,150 --> 00:16:02,170
Your family pride
won't put any food

331
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:04,260
on your table for you.

332
00:16:04,260 --> 00:16:07,200
But we have patiently
taught you how to make a living.

333
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:10,020
It doesn't matter to me
how dirty it may seem to you.

334
00:16:10,020 --> 00:16:13,010
As part of our family,
we will take care of you.

335
00:16:13,010 --> 00:16:15,080
But I've already
explained it earlier.

336
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,070
I don't want to do it anymore.

337
00:16:17,070 --> 00:16:20,140
You'd better watch your mouth
when you talk to komicho.

338
00:16:20,140 --> 00:16:22,200
You now what I think
of your samurai background?

339
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,120
It stinks.

340
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:24,210
Your dad was stupid to oppose

341
00:16:24,210 --> 00:16:25,210
the government's army

342
00:16:25,210 --> 00:16:27,220
and your mom must've
been brainless, too.

343
00:16:36,170 --> 00:16:38,120
My father sacrificed his life

344
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:40,070
in order to protect
his feudal lord,

345
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:42,030
my mother worked hard
to raise me right.

346
00:16:42,030 --> 00:16:45,120
They taught me to be
proud of who I am.

347
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:49,060
That's why I don't allow
anyone to badmouth my parents!

348
00:16:49,060 --> 00:16:50,080
Got it?

349
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:54,030
And I won't work
for you ever again!

350
00:16:54,030 --> 00:16:56,130
I see.

351
00:16:56,130 --> 00:16:58,140
Well, Gasuke, Yoshi
is your property,

352
00:16:58,140 --> 00:17:03,070
but I think it's time
to let go of him.

353
00:17:03,070 --> 00:17:04,150
I have to cut my losses.

354
00:17:04,150 --> 00:17:08,030
♪

355
00:17:08,030 --> 00:17:09,140
Stop!

356
00:17:09,140 --> 00:17:10,200
There's no need for bloodshed.

357
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:16,000
♪

358
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,040
-Huh?
-Huh?

359
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:20,090
Hey!

360
00:17:20,090 --> 00:17:21,280
I finally found you.

361
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:25,100
So, just who the hell are
you to come bursting in here?

362
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:26,060
Well?

363
00:17:26,060 --> 00:17:27,110
Who are you?

364
00:17:27,110 --> 00:17:28,110
Answer!

365
00:17:28,110 --> 00:17:29,160
Men, get in here!

366
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:31,010
We've got ourselves an intruder!

367
00:17:31,010 --> 00:17:35,000
♪

368
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,180
Your men won't be coming.

369
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:38,260
They weren't very hospitable
when I asked to come in,

370
00:17:38,260 --> 00:17:40,130
so I had to teach them a lesson

371
00:17:40,130 --> 00:17:43,210
and I put those rude guys
to sleep for a little while.

372
00:17:43,210 --> 00:17:44,160
Really?

373
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:46,160
Who are you?

374
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:49,060
I am Kenshin Himura
the Wanderer.

375
00:17:49,060 --> 00:17:51,080
I have come here
to retrieve my friend Kori

376
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:52,270
and the boy Yoshi
so we can go back

377
00:17:52,270 --> 00:17:54,130
where we belong.

378
00:17:54,130 --> 00:17:55,120
You shoulda stayed at home!

379
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:56,150
You made a mistake!

380
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:58,020
Time to say goodbye!

381
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:06,050
I was still talking.

382
00:18:06,050 --> 00:18:08,020
You need to learn
not to interrupt people.

383
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:15,040
Whoa.

384
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:17,000
Sorry about your roof.

385
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,120
Before that interruption,
I wanted to ask you to show

386
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:21,260
your generosity
of spirit, komicho.

387
00:18:21,260 --> 00:18:23,270
Release my two friends, please.

388
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:25,080
I think it's
a better choice for you

389
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:26,230
than losing all your men,

390
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:27,150
don't you agree?

391
00:18:27,150 --> 00:18:31,140
♪

392
00:18:31,140 --> 00:18:32,200
Sure!

393
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:35,180
Please, I'd appreciate it
if you'd take them and go!

394
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:39,010
Thank you,
you're very generous.

395
00:18:39,010 --> 00:18:41,090
Let's go home,
you were hard to find.

396
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:43,200
I'm glad you finally showed up.

397
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,210
Are you all right?

398
00:18:44,210 --> 00:18:48,030
♪

399
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:50,040
Why'd you have to come
barging into my life?

400
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:53,010
Needed to do
a little charity work?

401
00:18:53,010 --> 00:18:54,240
I do fine on my own!

402
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:57,120
Hey, Yoshi, you like
to handle things your way,

403
00:18:57,120 --> 00:19:00,060
but I couldn't leave something
this important to chance.

404
00:19:00,060 --> 00:19:03,050
Okay, I apologize if my
actions cramp your style,

405
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:04,280
but you're coming
with me right now.

406
00:19:04,280 --> 00:19:06,220
-Hey!
-Let's go.

407
00:19:06,220 --> 00:19:08,040
You're not leaving!

408
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:10,250
Yes, let them
leave now, you idiots!

409
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:12,090
He has the eyes of an assassin!

410
00:19:12,090 --> 00:19:13,240
He's not the kind
that will just kill

411
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:18,070
out of malice, but you
saw how he dealt with Gasuke!

412
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:20,250
Those eyes...I never thought
I'd see such a man in this

413
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:23,140
new Meiji era.

414
00:19:23,140 --> 00:19:25,240
You mark my words,
if he ever gets serious,

415
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:28,020
he won't leave us just sleeping!

416
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:29,130
When he gets through,
there won't be enough

417
00:19:29,130 --> 00:19:31,060
of you left to count the bodies.

418
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:33,080
We'll let him have
the boy, it's a small price,

419
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:36,170
but he will someday
pay for what he did.

420
00:19:36,170 --> 00:19:40,130
Someday...he will pay.

421
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:49,060
Darn it!

422
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:53,290
♪

423
00:19:53,290 --> 00:19:55,270
So, why are you still
beating yourself up

424
00:19:55,270 --> 00:20:00,260
about not being able to handle
everything yourself, huh?

425
00:20:00,260 --> 00:20:03,190
I wish I could've handled it.

426
00:20:03,190 --> 00:20:05,040
I tried to be
as strong as I could,

427
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:07,130
but it just wasn't enough!

428
00:20:07,130 --> 00:20:08,240
Thanks for saving me.

429
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:10,010
Even though my parents are gone,

430
00:20:10,010 --> 00:20:12,130
I still wanna make them proud.

431
00:20:12,130 --> 00:20:13,070
You will.

432
00:20:13,070 --> 00:20:17,040
♪

433
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:18,120
Well, we finally made it.

434
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:21,170
♪

435
00:20:21,170 --> 00:20:24,180
Welcome to your new home.

436
00:20:24,180 --> 00:20:25,170
You mean it?

437
00:20:25,170 --> 00:20:26,270
Really?

438
00:20:26,270 --> 00:20:28,110
And while you're
staying with us,

439
00:20:28,110 --> 00:20:31,100
you will be learning
the martial art, kendo.

440
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:32,070
Huh?

441
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:34,000
Martial arts?

442
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:36,040
It will help you be stronger.

443
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:38,220
Mm-hmm!

444
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:40,150
Yeah, I'll be the best swordsman

445
00:20:40,150 --> 00:20:42,280
this dojo's ever had!

446
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:45,110
And you will have
the best kendo teacher ever,

447
00:20:45,110 --> 00:20:49,170
a Kamiya Kasshin-style
swordmaster, Ms. Kori Kamiya.

448
00:20:49,170 --> 00:20:51,170
So, what are you babbling about?

449
00:20:51,170 --> 00:20:52,180
Huh?

450
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:54,230
You gotta be kidding me!

451
00:20:54,230 --> 00:20:56,190
Having her as
a teacher's extreme!

452
00:20:56,190 --> 00:20:59,070
She's so ugly!

453
00:20:59,070 --> 00:21:02,080
All right, just because
I do not have any pupils

454
00:21:02,080 --> 00:21:04,040
does not mean I have to--

455
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:05,080
Kori?

456
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:07,010
Just listen,
I'm the one that says when

457
00:21:07,010 --> 00:21:08,260
and who I'll teach, you got it?

458
00:21:08,260 --> 00:21:10,200
Hey, I'd like to see you
spank me if you can,

459
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,240
you big raccoon-face!

460
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:16,280
♪

461
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:17,220
I'll get you!

462
00:21:17,220 --> 00:21:20,140
♪

463
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:22,270
Raccoon!

464
00:21:22,270 --> 00:21:23,270
You're through!

465
00:21:23,270 --> 00:21:27,140
♪

466
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:30,030
And that's how it happened
that an orphan named Yoshi

467
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:33,250
from a samurai family
became a member of our family

468
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:35,120
and joined the Kamiya dojo.

469
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:39,290
♪

470
00:21:41,708 --> 00:23:25,140
♪

